CAPE TOWN - The City of Cape Town is proposing to erect another statue to honour the late Nelson Mandela on the iconic balcony where he first addressed the country as a free man.The city is calling for public participation before going ahead with the plan.The statue will be complemented by a permanent exhibition that will also recognise other struggle heroes.READ: Madiba statue a sign of apartheid's defeat - JacksonThe proposed project is to be rolled out in conjunction with what would have been the former president s 100th birthday.City of Cape Town Mayor Patricia de Lille said, "Public comments will remain open until the 21st of May for people to make their views heard."*View the attached video for more on this story